metadata.name: Digital Images for Analog Eyes #46
metadata.description:
An attempt at capturing a uniquely digital aesthetic in code-generated images.
Alternatively this is just experimentation with color, noise and the modulo operator.

Details may vary per device, aspect ratio and window size

Generative images by @0x3739
Visuals are code-generated
library: twgljs - A Tiny WebGL helper Library
License: CC-BY-NC-SA 4.0

controls
'-' to zoom in.
'+' to zoom out.
'k' to decompose/pixelize the image.
Can take up to 10 decomposing steps before the effect is visible.
'8' or 'arrow_up' to move up in the image.
'5' or 'arrow_down' to move down in the image.
'6' or 'arrow_right' to move right in the image.
'4' or 'arrow_left' to move left in the image.
'1,f,w,a' to change the aspect ratio.
's' to save an image of the canvas.
'h' to increase the quality modifier (maximum is 5).
'l' to decrease the quality modifier (minimum is 1).
The quality modifier is a modifier on the width and height of the canvas.
Changing the modifier can affect the look of the image due to subpixel artifacts.
Use the modifier to save higher resolution images.

metadata.name: uncurated_pico_punks.p8 #176
metadata.description:
pico_punks is a community-curated, shared royalty, generative pfp project on the Tezos blockchain, developed on the Pico-8 Fantasy Console. Each pico_punk is uniquely generated purely from code, by displaying p8scii characters on the screen.

This fx(hash) pico_punk generator is based on "pico_punk_generator.p8" and "pico_punks_infinite.p8". It has a 50% chance to use either generator as a base. Each has been modified to permit any combination of Pico-8 colors.

The full set of curated pico_punks can be found here: https://versum.xyz/board/8Dt3fAfO8

For more pico_punks, follow @pico_punks on twitter! 



creator: Andrew E. Brereton
date: 2022-03-08
twitter: @aebrer
website: aebrer.xyz
medium: Pico-8, Lua

metadata.name: Moonlines #5
metadata.description:
The Moonlines project explores the combination of minimalist forms and basic rules to create complex images.

It uses a simplistic approach to combine 4 sets of parallel lines and a main shape in its center.

The overlapping and intersection of slightly slanted lines can generate beautiful interferences that result in complex moiré effects.

Artist: Estienne
March 2022
NFT 2.0 License

metadata.name: orGANics #4
metadata.description:
Experimental generative composition using images created with Artbreeder.

Microbes, bacterias, viruses, fungi, eyes, nebulars, etc. are distributed over three layers to illustrate the similarities between the microscopic and the macroscopic.

Composed in p5js.

Hit 's' in live view to save a .png

All images created with Artbreeder are public domain (CC0).

metadata.name: Hexagones - Art for Bots for Humans #36
metadata.description:
For (some) Humans.

"Hexagones - Art for Bots for Humans", also known as "HAFBFH", "HA4B4H", and "HA4B4HY2KLIGCVEd" (Hexagones - Art For Bots For Humans Y2K Light Industries Genesis Contract Variable Edition), is an airdrop project for owners (who I assume are all bots) of the original "Hexagones - Art for Bots" project, a snapshot of which was taken at 4:30 pm on a sunny Monday afternoon, 14th March 2022 in the UK.

This is a prequel to "Hexagones - Art for Bots for Humans for Print" project, which will appear on the new contract, following a similar but not identical design.

Instructions ::

1-0, '-' & '=' - Toggle various layers
m - Toggle the main hexagon
f - 30 second Flickr mode
h - Toggle high-res
s - Download and save image
